# AUTO-TAX env examples
#
# Local development:
# - Use .env.local.example as the template.
# - For `npm run dev`, copy it to `.env` because the Node server loads `.env`.
# - Vite-only overrides may go in `.env.local`.
#
# Vercel deployment:
# - Use .env.vercel.example as the dashboard checklist.
# - Do not commit real `.env` or `.env.local` files.
